7 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 63 O.S. 2021, Section 427.7, is
8 amended to read as follows:
9 Section 427.7. A. The Oklahoma Medical Marijuana Authority
10 shall create a medical marijuana use registry of patients and
11 caregivers as provided under this section. The handling of any
12 records maintained in the registry shall comply with all applicable
13 state and federal privacy laws.
14 B. The medical marijuana use registry shall be accessible to:
15 1. Oklahoma-licensed medical marijuana dispensaries to verify
16 the license of a patient or caregiver by the twenty-four-character
17 twelve-character identifier and PDF417 barcode; and
18 2. Any court in this state.
19 C. All other records regarding a medical marijuana patient or
20 caregiver licensee shall be maintained by the Authority and shall be
21 deemed confidential. The handling of any records maintained by the
22 Authority shall comply with all applicable state and federal privacy
23 laws. Such records shall be marked as confidential, shall not be
24 made available to the public, and shall only be made available to
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB774 SFLR Page 7
